I highly recommend this place! I tried it for Restaurant Week and was not disappointed.  They had a great selection of local beer. Their wings were a 4.5 out of 5 on my scale, and I'm very picky about wings.  The sauce was a perfect mix of heat with a little sweet.  The Lone Star burger was perfectly cooked and delicious.  And I loved their mason jar brownie sundae.  My only wish was for a more engaged waiter.  He came to the table, but never really asked if we needed anything or how our food was. Otherwise I will definitely be back to try the other burgers.

